00:00:24,380 --> 00:00:27,880
There is something I need to say to you, CEO.

4
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:31,450
 It's important. Please spare me some time. 

5
00:00:35,380 --> 00:00:39,050
 ♫ I see you again over time  ♫ 

6
00:00:39,050 --> 00:00:40,850
 Noona! 

7
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:47,010
 ♫ I recognize you at once ♫ 

8
00:00:50,890 --> 00:00:52,650
- Do Gyeom. 
 - Let's go.

9
00:00:52,650 --> 00:00:54,990
I found important evidence. I need to see the CEO.

10
00:00:54,990 --> 00:00:59,720
Later. Talk to him later.

11
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:05,150
 ♫ No one else can, I'm not waiting ♫  

12
00:01:05,150 --> 00:01:09,730
 ♫ I love you ♫  

13
00:01:09,730 --> 00:01:15,990
 ♫ Even if I feel bad for waiting ♫  

14
00:01:15,990 --> 00:01:20,790
 ♫ No moment without you ♫  

15
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:24,970
 ♫ I don’t like it, I hate it ♫  

16
00:01:24,970 --> 00:01:28,390
 ♫ Our breakup ♫  

17
00:01:28,390 --> 00:01:34,030
 ♫ still seems like a lie ♫ 

18
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,250
Secretary Nam,

19
00:01:45,250 --> 00:01:49,180
can we start today's plan earlier?

20
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:51,370
 - I'm being followed?  
 - Yes.

21
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:52,920
I saw it when I was getting out of the taxi.

22
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:57,160
It's the same car that was in front of Team Leader Kim Hyeon Soo's house.

23
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:59,510
The director probably ordered it, right?

24
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:04,500
I talked to Team Leader Kim Hyeon Soo's younger sibling.

25
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,050
Did you find anything?

26
00:02:06,050 --> 00:02:07,730
He left for Australia yesterday.

27
00:02:07,730 --> 00:02:10,410
He didn't say exactly where he was going and what was going on.

28
00:02:10,410 --> 00:02:13,390
He just asked him to take care of the apartment.

29
00:02:13,390 --> 00:02:17,080
I found the culprit who stole the contract from the office.

30
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:20,480
How? There was no suspicious person even on the CCTV.

31
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,090
   

32
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:30,100
- Hello? 
  - I would like to meet you right now. 

33
00:03:23,730 --> 00:03:25,850
Hey, Mister.

34
00:03:25,850 --> 00:03:27,460
How can you suddenly press the brake?

35
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:30,440
What are you talking about right now?

36
00:03:33,310 --> 00:03:34,850
Where are you going right now when you caused an accident?

37
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:37,290
- Call your insurance company! 
 - I need to go!

38
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:40,480
Where are you going? It's going to be a hit and run.

39
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:46,220
CEO, it seems what you ordered is going as planned.

40
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:50,220
As soon as the insurance company collects the black box, I will get it and check the footage.

41
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:54,120
Since they're close with Director Kim, it's probably Team Manager Kim Hyeon Soo or the investigative team

42
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:58,260
that approached. We can only hope that there is evidence left.

43
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:00,840
How much time can you buy?

44
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,210
About 30 minutes.

45
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:06,880
Also, what would you like to do about the emergency shareholder's meeting?

46
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,270
Please proceed as planned.

47
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:15,350
You lost Seo Hyeon Joo? What do you mean?

48
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,270
I understand. Finish that matter quickly

49
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:22,570
and go to Seo Hyeon Joo's house.

50
00:04:22,570 --> 00:04:26,430
If she arrives later than you, then it's clear she did something in between her trip.

51
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:28,800
Please report back quickly.

52
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:12,710
 I found it. 

53
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:16,290
It was the internal investigative team that switched the contract.

54
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:19,720
Can't we prove with this that the back-end contract was fabricated?

55
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,130
Also, that this was the director's doing?

56
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:24,820
I will find out the truth about this. Please don't investigate anymore.

57
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:27,450
Also, don't come looking for me like today.

58
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:30,410
Why? Because the director will find out?

59
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:32,650
Can't she?

60
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:39,370
I will try to talk to her about why she is doing this to us.

61
00:05:39,370 --> 00:05:41,520
It's less frustrating when we know the reason behind her action.

62
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,170
Please leave.

63
00:05:43,170 --> 00:05:49,010
Kim Soo Jeong had the music box you gave me.

64
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:11,610
I went after I received the note to retrieve the music box but the store owner didn't have it.

65
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:16,100
I saw Kim Soo Jeong paying the man

66
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:18,300
who gave me the note.

67
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:21,300
Kim Soo Jeong sent the note?

68
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,680
How do you know that, CEO?

69
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:32,610
I saw it by chance in the student lounge. That's all.

70
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,180
CEO!

71
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:19,860
 Team Leader Seo is currently at home. 

72
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:26,630
Just in case, tell the person tailing her to be careful.

73
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:32,260
Before this matter is closed, don't lose sight of Seo Hyeon Joo.

74
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,930
In order for Kim Soo Jeong to snatch this,

75
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:42,850
she sent a fake note.

76
00:07:45,210 --> 00:07:47,230
But why?

77
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:05,590
 Kim Soo Jeong had the music box you gave me. 

78
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:11,270
 I went after I received the note to retrieve the music box but the store owner didn't have it. 

79
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:13,380
 You made this, right? 

80
00:08:13,380 --> 00:08:15,070
     

81
00:08:18,330 --> 00:08:24,430
  I saw Kim Soo Jeong paying the man who gave me the note. 

82
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:28,720
 This was all Director Kim's doing. 

83
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:50,900
 CEO, if I had gone to the location where we were supposed to meet, 

84
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:54,860
 would things have been different? 

85
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:16,970
  

86
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:42,080
My daughter, where are you? Are you on your way to work?

87
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,790
 Yes, Mom. Is something wrong? 

88
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:46,810
Nothing. I was just wondering about your well-being.

89
00:09:46,810 --> 00:09:49,600
- Nothing's wrong, right? 
  - Of course. 

90
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,770
 Don't worry. 

91
00:09:51,770 --> 00:09:54,170
Okay. Be careful when you drive.

92
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:56,360
 Okay. 

93
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:05,210
Is she saying nothing's wrong because she doesn't want us to worry or because everything is really all right?

94
00:10:05,210 --> 00:10:10,380
It's good if there is nothing wrong; however, you never know what will happen in the future.

95
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:14,980
For now, let's prepare the money we need to reimburse the company for.

96
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:17,660
They wouldn't sue us if we reimburse them.

97
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:22,190
It's a billion won ($1 million). Do we even have that?

98
00:10:22,190 --> 00:10:26,540
I don't know about selling the house but with the small land we have and

99
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:30,680
all the savings, it won't even be enough to cover half.

100
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:34,020
Should I find a job at a supermarket?

101
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:36,990
For now, let's

102
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:40,300
gather everything we have.

103
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:48,100
We have nothing even if we try to gather anything we have.

104
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:26,290
This is an emergency fund I saved for more than 10 years.

105
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:31,710
Goodness. How much is this?

106
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:36,790
Why did you say you didn't have anything back then?

107
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:38,290
When?

108
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:42,510
Two years ago, I asked you for some money for the trip abroad with my friends and you said you didn't even have a penny.

109
00:11:42,510 --> 00:11:46,150
Did you not say that?

110
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:47,040
I don't remember.

111
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,180
You also said that last winter.

112
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:52,350
When I asked you to buy the coat I had my eyes on because it was on sale,

113
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:55,210
you took off your thermal undergarments because you didn't have money.

114
00:11:55,210 --> 00:11:59,420
Do you think we will have any money if I gave you money for a trip abroad and a coat?

115
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:00,990
Is that important right now?

116
00:12:00,990 --> 00:12:05,200
The important fact is that you hid money from me and pretended to be dirt poor.

117
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,440
- I'm taking this. 
 - You can't.

118
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,970
When others were buying brand name clothes,

119
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:12,860
I gathered this money by wearing socks with holes.

120
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:16,260
I'm the one who sewed up those socks.

121
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:20,510
If I catch you hiding emergency funds from me one more time,

122
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:24,930
I'm going to kick you out with just underwear with holes in it.

123
00:12:24,930 --> 00:12:26,340
What are you doing right now?

124
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:28,820
Let go! Let go!

125
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:31,350
I worked so hard to save this money!

126
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:36,410
Is it that expensive to sew up the holes in my socks?

127
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:44,300
Geez, look at you go.

128
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:46,680
I knew you were going to act like this,

129
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:51,940
so I hid more emergency funds from you.

130
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:29,130
There are less than ten days until the platform launching.

131
00:13:29,130 --> 00:13:33,030
You have to hand in ten chapters of saved manuscripts by this week.

132
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:34,890
Our team is not disbanding, right?

133
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:39,540
I heard today was the emergency shareholder's meeting. If by any chance, the CEO changes...

134
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:43,340
I don't think they will put a stop to a business that has come this far.

135
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:48,290
I believe the webtoon business will proceed as is.

136
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:51,790
I understand your worries, but at times like this, we have to believe each other

137
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,920
and work hard on our jobs.

138
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,840
- We believe you, Team Leader. 
 - Me, too.

139
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,180
- We believe you. 
 - We believe you.

140
00:13:57,180 --> 00:13:59,020
We can do this!

141
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:05,720
But Producer Pal Do is late today, too.

142
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:10,320
You're right. He's never late because he doesn't want to be on the bad side of the people higher up.

143
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:13,800
There's trouble, Team Leader.

144
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:14,960
Is something wrong?

145
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,920
CEO... CEO...

146
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,630
Stop being dramatic and spit it out.

147
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:21,430
What about CEO?

148
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:23,750
He's going to the American branch.

149
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:26,750
Los Angeles. L.A.!

150
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:29,120
- You sure you heard right? 
 - Yes!

151
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:33,740
I heard from the transfer department. How can the CEO...

152
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:44,870
What's going on?

153
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:49,060
I thought we could clear our name with the evidence we found.

154
00:14:50,110 --> 00:14:51,810
That's possible.

155
00:14:51,810 --> 00:14:54,830
Then there's no need for the CEO to resign.

156
00:14:54,830 --> 00:14:57,720
What's with being sent to the American branch?

157
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:04,220
If you need me, call me. I'll be outside.

158
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,850
     

159
00:15:30,020 --> 00:15:33,620
     

160
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:40,780
     

161
00:16:02,060 --> 00:16:07,860
    
   

162
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:14,620
    

163
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:28,540
 Then, what is troubling you the most, CEO Hwang? 

164
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:35,730
 The guilt of making my loved one unhappy three times. 

165
00:16:35,730 --> 00:16:38,760
 She died in pain... 

166
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:40,730
 because of me. 

167
00:16:40,730 --> 00:16:46,290
 All three times were inevitable. 

168
00:17:12,590 --> 00:17:14,500
  I found it. 

169
00:17:26,450 --> 00:17:29,040
  This is the contract Team Leader Seo Hyeon Joo signed. 

170
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,730
 Did you prepare the back-end contract? 

171
00:17:31,730 --> 00:17:34,130
  Yes. I copied the signature on it. 

172
00:17:34,130 --> 00:17:35,930
 It's a flight for tomorrow at 9:00. 

173
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:39,580
 I will give you the promised money at the airport parking lot. 

174
00:17:41,420 --> 00:17:45,000
   

175
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:47,430
    
    

176
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:51,720
He was imprisoned for over a year for student demonstrations?

177
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:55,840
   

178
00:18:58,410 --> 00:19:01,690
 Did you hear? Senior Jin Ho was a mole for the police. 

179
00:19:01,690 --> 00:19:03,720
 Really? Why didn't they arrest us? 

180
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,120
 You're wrong. I heard he went abroad with a girl. 

181
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:08,930
 A person in my department saw him getting in a car with a pretty girl. 

182
00:19:08,930 --> 00:19:11,750
 Really? I'm jealous. 

183
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:19,490
I assume you saw the video I sent you.

184
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:26,220
You should prepare yourself because you will be under investigation with the police soon.

185
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:32,100
You dare deceive me and stab me in the back?

186
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:35,710
Do you even have the right to say that?

187
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:41,600
So many years passed and you changed your name yet nothing changed.

188
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:44,200
I thought you would at least be repenting and regretting.

189
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,640
Repenting?

190
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,820
What should I be repenting about?

191
00:19:47,820 --> 00:19:51,230
There is no past you can keep hidden.

192
00:19:52,420 --> 00:19:55,000
You reported Song Min Joo to the police, right?

193
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,380
You were going to capture her with the fake letter,

194
00:19:57,380 --> 00:20:01,410
but Kang Jin Ho appeared and everything failed.

195
00:20:01,410 --> 00:20:06,040
Even your despicable tactics haven't changed.

196
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,940
What else did you do to them both?

197
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:14,000
 The police had the poster Min Joo made. 

198
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:17,040
 If I didn't confess, Min Joo would've been arrested. 

199
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:18,740
 I didn't have time to hesitate. 

200
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:23,220
 Min Joo was on her way to the music box store. 

201
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:33,040
   

202
00:21:07,780 --> 00:21:09,720
 Song Min Joo? 

203
00:21:53,670 --> 00:21:57,200
    

204
00:22:05,550 --> 00:22:09,410
 I stole the ring and sent it to Min Joo. 

205
00:22:09,410 --> 00:22:14,460
I wrote her a letter to not wait.

206
00:22:14,460 --> 00:22:19,020
So Min Joo went to Woo Yeong.

207
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:25,640
If it was me, I would have waited until the end.

208
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:28,530
That must've been the extent of her feelings for him.

209
00:22:28,530 --> 00:22:30,700
It must be.

210
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:35,460
Those events aren't really important to me.

211
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:39,630
You will be punished by law for the things you did now.

212
00:22:39,630 --> 00:22:43,370
But how will you get forgiveness for the things you'd done in the past?

213
00:22:43,370 --> 00:22:46,100
How is informing Min Joo a sin?

214
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:48,290
It's not a sin.

215
00:22:49,390 --> 00:22:52,800
There is nothing I need to ask for forgiveness.

216
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,090
You killed them.

217
00:22:55,800 --> 00:23:00,760
Kang Jin Ho, Min Joo, and Woo Yeong.

218
00:23:03,030 --> 00:23:04,610
What?

219
00:23:25,790 --> 00:23:29,790
 Your jealousy started the tragedy. 

220
00:23:35,670 --> 00:23:37,730
 Senior Jin Ho. 

221
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:51,740
 Are you okay? 

222
00:23:52,950 --> 00:23:54,450
 Senior. 

223
00:23:54,450 --> 00:23:56,250
 Please. 

224
00:23:58,710 --> 00:24:00,670
 Just go. 

225
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:07,390
 Kang Jin Ho died because of the aftereffects of torture. 

226
00:24:08,220 --> 00:24:12,060
 What did you just say? 

227
00:24:15,510 --> 00:24:17,530
 Senior. 

228
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,770
 Senior! 

229
00:24:42,210 --> 00:24:44,870
The two of them died due to a car accident.

230
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:49,980
If Kang Jin Ho wasn't arrested, these events wouldn't have happened.

231
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:53,040
Don't you think so?

232
00:24:55,710 --> 00:24:59,970
 I heard the accident happened when she heard Senior Jin Ho died. 

233
00:24:59,970 --> 00:25:03,690
 No! No. 

234
00:25:03,690 --> 00:25:06,280
You killed her.

235
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:08,630
Yourself, too.

236
00:25:08,630 --> 00:25:14,390
Min Joo, Woo Yeong, and everyone else, too. Also, you're the one who made me like this.

237
00:25:15,730 --> 00:25:18,530
Even at the dying moment,

238
00:25:18,530 --> 00:25:21,160
if you hadn't ignored me so coldly,

239
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:24,400
we wouldn't have met like this.

240
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:29,020
Everything is because of you.

241
00:25:31,470 --> 00:25:33,520
So it's my fault.

242
00:25:35,430 --> 00:25:38,930
If I knew Kim Soo Jeong was this weak and pitiful,

243
00:25:38,930 --> 00:25:44,820
I would have apologized and hugged her saying don't be hurt.

244
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:48,540
I'm pitiful?

245
00:25:48,540 --> 00:25:50,550
Stop kidding yourself.

246
00:25:51,340 --> 00:25:54,450
I will make you regret saying that.

247
00:25:54,450 --> 00:25:59,950
You haven't won yet.

248
00:25:59,950 --> 00:26:02,700
I take back saying you

249
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:05,090
should put the past in the past.

250
00:26:05,090 --> 00:26:09,140
Stay in the hell of the past...

251
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:12,800
forever.

252
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:21,790
I didn't kill them.

253
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:25,770
It's not because of me.

254
00:26:25,770 --> 00:26:28,970
Why do I have to hear these things?

255
00:26:28,970 --> 00:26:30,810
Why me?

256
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:46,890
